Aim   : Install DHCP Server 
Theory: DHCP stands for dynamic host configuration protocol & it's a network protocol that use for on a ip network
        i.e  a DHCP server automatically  assign ip address and other info  to each host on the network
        so they can communicate with other point.
        

Steps->

Step1:Command-install dhcp-server:-  $sudo apt install -y isc-dhcp-server

Step2:Now we configure dhcpd.conf by directly editing through a path :- $sudo nano /etc/dhcp/dhcpd.conf

Step3:finding machine ip address by:- $ip a (or)  $ip addr

Step4: then configure the subnet  and the netmask -- then save the file or exit

Step5:now we are enable the services using this command:- $sudo systemctl enable isc-dhcp-server.service

Step6:start the service :- $sudo systemctl start isc-dhcp-server.service

Step7:stop the service :- $sudo systemctl stop isc-dhcp-server.service




